Package: fastText
Type: Package
Title: Efficient Learning of Word Representations and Sentence Classification
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2019-07-14
Authors@R: c( person("Lampros", "Mouselimis", email = "mouselimislampros@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")), person("Facebook", "Inc", role = "cph") )
Maintainer: Lampros Mouselimis <mouselimislampros@gmail.com>
Description: An interface to the 'fastText' <https://github.com/facebookresearch/fastText> library for efficient learning of word representations and sentence classification. For more information, see (i) "Enriching Word Vectors with Subword Information" by Bojanowski, Piotr and Grave, Edouard and Joulin, Armand and Mikolov, Tomas (2017), <doi:10.1162/tacl_a_00051>; (ii) "Bag of Tricks for Efficient Text Classification" by Joulin, Armand and Grave, Edouard and Bojanowski, Piotr and Mikolov, Tomas (2017), <doi:10.18653/v1/e17-2068>; (iii) "FastText.zip: Compressing text classification models" by Joulin, Armand and Grave, Edouard and Bojanowski, Piotr and Douze, Matthijs and Jégou, Hérve and Mikolov, Tomas (2016), <arXiv:1612.03651>.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
SystemRequirements: Generally, fastText builds on modern Mac OS and Linux distributions. Since it uses some C++11 features, it requires a compiler with good C++11 support. These include a (g++-4.7.2 or newer) or a (clang-3.3 or newer).
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: Rcpp (>= 1.0.0), ggplot2, grid, utils
Depends: R(>= 3.2.3)
LinkingTo: Rcpp
Suggests: testthat, covr,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
VignetteBuilder: knitr
